                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-550" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-550" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-550" type="surname" value="SIMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-550" type="given" value="JOHN THOMAS"></interp>JOHN THOMAS SIMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I deal in furniture, and live in Cleveland-street, Marylebone. On the morning of the 8th of May, about twenty minutes to nine o'clock, I left my shop for not more than two minutes—as I came back</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184305080079"></xptr>
               <p>I saw the prisoner with a mattress on his shoulder, just leaving my shop—I said, "You had better take that mattress to where you took it from"—he said, "Where is that, sir?"—I said, "You know as well as I do; take it back again"—he immediately turned round, and took it back to the shop—I went for a policeman, and gave him in charge—I had left the mattress in the shop when I went out—it is worth about 25<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—this now produced is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was employed to carry it. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I did not employ him to take it—I had not sold it to any body.</p>
